O serviço é simpático e rápido. Pela relação qualidade preço, só não merece as 5 estrelas porque está normalmente muito cheio e o ambiente fica demasiado ruidoso.

Gestern, Mittwoch, 17.September erreichten wir gemäss 50'000Landeskarte die Seilbahnstation Strichboden. Wir sahen nur den Schopf und die zweri Tragseile zu Tal gleiten. Zweim MItwadnerer standen davor. Da wir keinerlei Anschlag zur Bahn vorfanden, fragten wir die beiden. Und siehe da,
nach 10 Minuten durftemn wir ins abenteuerliche Gefährt einstuegen und die schwindelerregende Talfahrt geniessen. Derwährend merkte unser Mitpassagir, dass er den Rucksack mitsamt Portemonnaie usw.oben hatte liegen lassen. Denn er war selber so fasziniert von der Bahn, dass er nur sein Handy dabei hatte. Unterwegs berieten wir zu viert, wass zu tun sei. Unten angekommen, beichtete der Fahrgast sein Problem worauf der Bahnwärter ohne Zögern meinte"Dann fahren wir halt nochmals!". Und los ging die Auf- und NIederfahrt.  Und das in der sonst so geizhalsigen Schweiz!
Da kann ich nur meine höchsten Komplimente ausrufen udn danken!  Rudolf Meyer mit Ruth Stutz-Frey.

Empfehlenswertes Restaurant mit ordentlichen Portionen zu guten Preisen. Obwohl der Wirt uns darauf hingewiesen hat, dass er an dem Tag alleine war, war das Essen recht schnell bereit. Der "extrem leckere" Burger war in der Tat sehr lecker.

Die Pommes sind wirklich gut, zum Teil vielleicht eine Spur zu salzig aber insgesamt gut.
Die Currywurst in Kombination mit der Soße war eher mittelmäßig, die Schicken Nuggets waren eher schlecht fast pappig, obwohl sie sogar frisch gemacht wurden.

Located in Bethlehem City Hall. Great option if you're close to here during business hours

Located indoors at the Bethlehem Transportation Center. Intended for riders of LANTA bus and other interstate buses. There are two newly renovated restrooms that are cleaned daily. Would be 5 stars if open longer hours.
Located in Main Street Commons, downstairs. Great option but you have to ask one of the businesses for the key.

Located at Bethlehem SkatePlaza along the South Bethlehem Greenway. Hasn't been open since 2012. Would be a great location if staffing could clean and maintain it daily.

Têm quatro zonas de serviço, o que é perfeito para o clima variável de Peniche: uma sala interior com assentos confortáveis, uma zona exterior coberta e envidraçada, uma outra coberta e ainda mais três mesas ao sol. O serviço é bom e simpático e normalmente rápido, exceto em dias de muito movimento.

Nicely located among old trees in the middle of a square in a posh part of Mokotów, in an art deco-style building of an art-house cinema. The coffee is solid, if not outstanding, but its main asset is the setting.
Good Food and nice staff.
For such a small fast food cafe, the meals are of amazing taste and quality. The food choice may be quite small but it's good enough for a quick meal after a long walk.
Comfortable atmosphere, very good pizza cooking, amazing food choice variety for a pizzeria.

It is located very close to the Highway so the noise level is relatively high. Other than that the RV sites have Power and Water hookups. A sanitary site is provided at the entrance. The bathrooms are clean and spacious and including showers. The staff is friendly and helpful.
Great spot for having a beer. The patio fronts the Sugar River and the lake. There's a limited food menu and carry-in food is allowed.
Very nice place, large selection of food but vegan options are rather limited.

Hatte zwei Trompeten zur Reparatur. Ging recht schnell und dazu noch ziemlich günstig. Die Qualität der Arbeit ist nicht zu beanstanden. Das Personal ist sehr freundlich und umgänglich. Ich kann das Geschäft uneingeschränkt weiter empfehlen.

Great for discovering new niche music. Automated channels work ok, but best to explore reposts and likes of already followed accounts. Fairly streamlined UX. Offline listening with premium account involved lots of manual work last time I checked, but may be better now.

Sehr gutes Fleisch vom heißen Stein. Preislich definitiv schon in der gehobenen Klasse, bedient wird man dementsprechend. Die Beilagen könnten ruhig größer sein. Die Auswahl der vegetarischen Gerichte beschränkt sich auf Beilagen und Salate.
Richtig uriges Kneipenkollektiv in einem leerstehenden Gebäude mit Hinterhof. Ein Besuch lohnt sich in jedem Fall!
Das Essen ist ganz gut, preislich im Mittelfeld. Das Ambiente ist etwas übertrieben "cool" und erzwugen, nicht urig oder ursprünglich. Da gibts definitiv schönere Bars in Budapest.

Sehr schönes Termalbad mit drei Außenbecken und vielen Innenbecken. Die eigentlich geltende Badekappen- und schlappenpflicht wird recht locker gehandhabt. Der Eintrittspreis von umgerechnet 10 Euro lohnt sich definitiv.
Ordentliche Pizza. Freundliche Bedienung. Etwas lang aufs Essen gewartet.

Nettes Restaurant mit tollem ungarischen Essen und (sehr) großen Portionen. Das Personal war stets freundlich und spricht Englisch und Ungarisch, teilweise auch Deutsch. Die Preise sind auf ungarischem Niveau. Manchmal gibt es auch traditionelle ungarische Hausmusik. Wenn man am Ende eines Abends viel Würfelglück hat, muss man sogar gar nichts bezahlen...

Lovely Tibetan restaurant with great traditional food. Run by a family, they really make an effort to make you a good evening. Nice for a date or casually eating. Love the momos and their udon noodles

As a student, I pay no entrance fee, so I go there really often. In the summer and with good weather there are many other people, but especially in the autumn, it is really nice. So many plants from all around the world and really silent everywhere, so you can easily relax from a hard day of work or something

A lovely Indian family who sells pizza and Indian food. The price is pretty low and the quality okay to good. You won't be blown away, but what you get for your money is really good, so I can recommend

Good supermarket for wholesale products. You need a card though, which you can only get with a business. They have pretty special things, but sometimes they dont even have basics, especially concerning vegetables. Furthermore, the prices can be pretty high, but I believe the quality is also better than in your typical supermarket
Great community of local hackers and knowledgeable people in the IT area. If you want to meet new people or learn something, just go there and ask someone!
The place does not look as nice as the others around it, but it has really good food and nice people. It surely is not cheap, but I think it is worth it
Great food for everyone with burgers, salads and really good fries etc. and the people are really lovely

The go-to marketplace for open-source android apps. Many different (and somewhat better) clients and has a really open structure. Sadly there is no rating or commenting system in place, but in combination with mangrove this might come in the future :)

Jobbed there once, was customer many times and referred many friends, family members and my own customers happy to this business. Really nice people that really know what they are doing. Can only recommend!

Thanks for checking out the demo! It is meant to showcase the tech, but is based on free and open APIs. The Nominatim (OSM) API is unfortunately sometimes down, which we can not do much about. We hope that if you spread the word, applications with access to more reliable location APIs will be debeloped!
Das sympathischste Café im Viertel. Hier haben wir unsere Hochzeit ausklingen lassen und alle Gäste waren begeistert.
Awesome idea, unfortunately still a little buggy - OSM places connector failing most of the time.
great!

Eine Bar in der es auch lecker Essen und Snacks mit wechselnder Karte gibt.
Im hinteren Zimmer kann man gut sitzen und es gibt auch diverse Brettspiele. Leider wird dort geraucht, aber im Sommer kann man bei gutem Wetter auch draußen sitzen.
Great day out and lovely steam train ride along the beautiful River Dart to the old town of Totnes.
Personnel accueillant, jamais eu de soucis sur les commandes ou livraisons.
Famous touristic location!
Quiet and lovely city, ideal for a historic trip. Lot's of activities for young kids, but lacks the young population population to make it dynamic

Funky interior, but low quality food. Sauces for rice dishes often contain only meat without any vegetable and noodle dishes do not have much taste. Better food and prices at Gotthärdli am See thai restaurant.
Easily accessible data about all kinds of topics. Includes interactive charts and ability to download in CSV. Great for casual analysis of different topics.

Private bank in Switzerland. Nice design of branches and service, but when it comes to anything touching their IT setup, its pretty bad. Repeated mistakes when registering changes to accounts, intermittent breakage of mobile app, outdated credit card points scheme where you are being mailed pieces of paper to collect.
They fail to be reliable in the most basic cases, either due to poor IT or lack of transparent rules.

Content: well-researched, comprehensive review of the current state of accumulation and usage of personal data by corporations and governments. Shows the dystopian future into which we might be headed if we don't make changes. Risk assessments could be more balanced though to show also the opportunities. 
Style: insights could be compressed into much less text. The length of the book and the sometimes pretentious writing style might make it less accessible to a broader audience, which is a pity.

We went here for breakfast and it turned out to be a real hidden gem in terms of coziness and beautiful interior. Food was ok, we had an omelette with pickled veggies, topped with grated cheese. The regular omelette without the pickles is probably better. Service was very nice and the atmosphere was relaxed and cheerful.

It is a very nice walk up Gellert Hill, through a large park with windy paths and sculptures along the way. On top, you have a fantastic view over Budapest. A variety of stalls offering drinks and snacks makes it a great afternoon or early evening tour, especially on a warm and sunny day.

Nice vegan restaurant serving vegan versions of traditional Hungarian meals and more. Great for anyone who wants to explore the local cuisine without meat. Interior was well-maintained but looked a bit old-fashioned. But the food and great service made up for it.

Cozy historical village on the Tihany peninsula on the northern shore of Lake Balaton. Very well maintained and a real tourist magnet for the whole of Hungary. The village's website offers a downloadable pocket guide, a video and even a virtual tour. Besides the beautiful landscape one can enjoy the relics of the folk architecture such as the peasant houses. Had a great traditional meal at the Gulyas Udvar Etterem. Might become very crowded during high season (in March it was perfect though).

Had lunch here during our visit of Tihany, a picturesque historical village on a peninsula of Lake Balaton. This restaurant might look very touristic from outside, but inside you find a truly traditional cozy place that serves simple and very well-made local food, such as the cod paprikas I had. The waiter was very engaged and pleasant, and helped us to find the right meal according to our tastes. It was a great experience.

Great restaurant serving traditional gulyas and paprikas. Elegant and cozy industrial-style interior. Had two vegetarian dishes: one with giant white beans, topped with a fried egg and fresh peppers and onions that was fantastic. Second dish was good, but the mushrooms were a bit watery, so it was not as great as the bean dish. Great white wine recommendation (Tokaji) that fit perfectly.

Went here for breakfast and loved the food! Creative vegetarian/vegan options. Had dishes with oven-roasted pumpkin and another one with sweet potato, topped with different veggies or eggs/salmon. The coffee was great, too. Interior is cozy and interesting with the gallery, but overall quite small. At some point there was a queue of people ordering directly at the counter, which filled up the whole room.

Large historic indoor market in Budapest, built in 1897 and renovated in 1997. The architecture alone is already worth a visit. Very nice to wander around the many food stalls with local produce or popular Hungarian food items, eateries, souvenir shops.
Recht teuer. Laugengebäck ist ordentlich.

Static website generator in Julia. Still new, but quite enjoyable to use. Makes it really easy to include evaluated Julia code including plots. Supports good chunk of markdown including some useful extensions. Reasonable defaults. Still a bit clunky in the CLI workflow and smaller tooling ecosystem than JS. Good for static sites if you are into Julia ecosystem.

Best federated, open source messaging app out there. Fairly easy to use, allows servers with customised rules, supports end to end encryption, flexible room membership. Still has some UX issues with key management for encrypted channel and with poor loading performance both on the web and mobile.

Nice dashboard for tracking coronavirus. Seems to make use of reliable data and plots daily changes as well as log-scale cases. It would greatly benefit from showing cases per capita (or 100000 residents), rather than just numbers per country. Also the graphs do not allow zoom or finer ticks (to better see the rates).

Nice language for scientific computing - good performance, flexible type system and descent meta-programming. Main issues are with packages: slow load-times and still small ecosystem them (though growing well thanks to the type system). Some syntax and structuring of projects with modules feels a bit hacky.

Cool shelter located 1700mts high on the top of Cerro Catedral with an amazing 12km hike passing through forests, hills, and cliffs with the flowers and clear water. It has it all for the beginner hikers. Great in Spring/Summer seasons, when you can see the forest in between at its best. Make sure to take water and a walking stick along with some snacks for the way. The last hour can be tricky, as it is super steep. Wanna sleep/camp there? book in advance: http://refugiofreybariloche.com/

If you are in Buenos Aires and want to get away from all the noise, this small town is the perfect place for a day of relax and history. Disputed between the Spanish and Portuguese Crowns until almost the end of the XVIII century, it is the perfect plan for a day (by boat from Bs As or car/bus from Montevideo), where you can see the colonial architecture and enjoy the food and the sun. Make sure to check the Raddisson Hotel's pool if it is too warm! :D

Almost all soccer clubs in Buenos Aires have restaurants: this is the typical Neighbourhood club restaurant in the city, where you will be able to grasp the neighbourhood culture and how much people care about their sports club - especially if they play soccer there! great food! good quality and very friendly staff! 

Not so good if you don't eat meat: they do not have so many options for vegetarians.

Great place to try good plates that combines the best of Argentinian and Italian food tradition - good environment and really cheap. Try the "milanesa" if you eat meat and the "canelones" if you are a vegetarian. After 9pm you will need to queue, so make sure to either book in advance or go beforehand - and be careful: the sizes are really big! you can definitely share a portion.

Great for groups, families and friends, if you are looking for something romantic this is not the place to go.

Definitely one of the best views in Bariloche, you can reach the top of cerro Campanario either by foot (easy level hike) or cablecar - the ticket is around 3 EUR. Definetely worth it if you want to check the lakes around Bariloche and get an idea of the extension of The Andes. 

The Cerro is right at the start of "Circuito Chico": a 24km road through mountains full of hiking trails. So a good idea is always to wake up early, get to the top fo the mountain, and at around 11am start the Circuito.
An extension to PostgreSQL for spacial data. Pretty good documentation and a lot of options. Things work as expected. Requires some understanding of the different geospatial representation formats.
Beautiful city, a lot of culture to explore. And fantastic selection of restaurants, from traditional Polish food to exotic options such as Peruvian.

Visited the castle in winter, so it was a bit cold. Can only imagine how amazing it must be on a sunny day, with the lake around and the walls warmed by the sun. It was a fantastic experience to wander through its many rooms, and discover historical artifacts from its history spanning a whole millennium. Was touched by the story of François Bonivard who was imprisoned there and inspired a poem of Lord Byron: The Prisoner of Chillon.

Great Peruvian fusion food, fantastic drinks, and nice atmosphere! Interior is decorated with a lot of wood, dark green colours, and plants. The red drink on the picture was a delicious, interesting non-alcoholic hot drink with fresh raspberry and rosemary.

Visited a wonderful organ concert in this church on Sunday 2nd Feb. The concert took place on the organ-gallery, a loft that can be reached over stairs. I was impressed with the acoustics and the quality of the performance. Learned later that the church has been designated to cultural and spiritual events, and as a place for community gatherings, under the name CityKircheZug. Will definitely visit other cultural events here in the future.

Visited the Van Gogh Alive exhibition at Maag yesterday. Great experience in terms of sound and light quality. From the outside and also inside the building could benefit from modernisation to make it more welcoming.
Very nice town to visit: beautiful old town, nice modern art museum, views on Rigi, Pilatus and the lake.

Beautiful and diverse.
Too corporate.
Uber cliquey.
Feels like a mono-culture sometimes merely because so many people do not talk to eachother or help out one another.
Growing and changing a lot.
I feel like a little more openness to establishing connections with different people is all this area actually needs.
They would greatly benefit from reviews for the apps, maybe can integrate with Mangrove :)

Pretty nice repository of open-source apps for Android. Its fairly easy to search and the app is continuously improving with better update and installation experience. Recommend for anyone who likes open-source, ad-free apps.

A blog framework which makes it easy to get started fast with reasonable defaults. There is a decent amount of themes and its pretty straight forward to customize them. Generates static sites making it suitable for easy hosting.
Pretty nice server framework in Rust, lets you use strong types and has pretty nice database integration. Still a bit immature in terms of CORS and API docs autogeneration.
Nice setting and staff. Reasonable prices.
Ordentliches Essen mit gutem Bier. Die Portionen könnten manchmal etwas größer sein.
That restaurant has just been recommended by a friend.

A Chinese restaurant in the heart of Zug, Suan Long is a good place for a meal and a beer with friends. Food is good but not amazing, and there are no original vegetarian dishes, but rather the type of options where meat was replaced with tofu. Staff is friendly but often looks tired. It can be quite smoky inside due to the open kitchen where a lot of frying is going on.

Great view from the spa area and chill out room, 1st floor, small building.

Very nice located at the lake.

They could improve with more healthy food on the menu.
Very interesting food, great service.

Descent set of component for Vue, but a lot of broken things in relation to layout customization. Recommend to quickly get running. Documentation is fairly good for individual components, but not necessarily how it all comes together. https://mangrove.reviews uses it at the time of writing.

I do not have much experience with other similar bundles, so take with grain of salt.
Speciality is Pizzas with thick bottom.

Bürgenstock is great for a day trip from Zurich, Luzern or Zug. Nice trails on top for walks, and amazing view over alps and Lake Lucerne. Also, quite a few fine dining restaurants around, as well as a spa.

Nice destination for a hike up from the town of Zug. Hike takes around 2 hours and gives a beautiful view on the Zuger lake. On top there is a restaurant with simple local food to enjoy before hiking back down again. Good views on the alps, on some days you can even see Eiger, Jungfrau and Mönch.

We are using Open Collective for our open-source, non-profit project to receive donations and to manage our finances transparently for all contributors to see where money comes from and where it goes. It works pretty well for us so far.

We had the two vegetarian options on the menu and they were both very interesting and refined dishes. A bit too much grains for us, especially in the mushroom porridge, but nevertheless balanced and interesting tastes. Atmosphere also nice with large glass windows and a minimalist retro decor.

I regularly eat at this fantastic Thai restaurant. They have a bar downstairs which the restaurant shouldn't be confused with. The food is pretty authentic and there are sufficient vegetarian options. The restaurant is located in a historic and well kept house that displays original wood covered walls, with windows towards the lake. A pleasure for the eye as well.

We hiked up to Gütsch on a winter afternoon when it was already getting dark. Had a beautiful view over Lucerne from there. The restaurant also looks very nice, but didn't have the time to visit it. 
Next time we will definitely visit the little sculpture park there as it seemed interesting (closes at 18:00). For the way down we took the little funicular. Definitely recommend for a day trip to Luzern.
Great global map data!

Great to see that mainstream media is showing true dedication for Privacy on the internet! Can totally recommend NYT's The Privacy Project newsletter and website. More people should be aware of the threats from privacy invasion and how to mitigate it. https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/opinion/internet-privacy-project.html?emc=edit_priv_20200205&nl=the-privacy%20project&te=1
